parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: To fill up, satisfy. Or empletho em-play'-tho; from en and the base of pleistos;to fill in, i.e. to satisfy.

parse: Verb - Present Participle Active - Accusative Masculine Plural
str2: To be hungry, needy, desire earnestly. From the same as penes; to famish; figuratively, to crave.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: From ek and apostello; to send away forth, i.e. to despatch, or to dismiss.

parse: Verb - Present Participle Active - Accusative Masculine Plural
str2: To become rich, be rich, abound in. From ploutizo; to be wealthy.
